WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.060
I'll focus on some of the recent data with nivolumab and AVD with the focus on some updates

00:00:08.060 --> 00:00:15.340
from the SWOG trial and also looking at how the real-world utilization is shaping up as.

00:00:15.340 --> 00:00:18.360
These are my disclosures.

00:00:18.360 --> 00:00:19.580
These are the two objectives.

00:00:19.580 --> 00:00:25.040
One is to go over three-year follow-up data from the SWOG study and then looking at real-world

00:00:25.040 --> 00:00:30.220
outcomes with nivo-AVD and advanced Hodgkin lymphoma.

00:00:30.220 --> 00:00:39.320
I think a lot of us are aware of this large cooperative group study that was conducted

00:00:39.320 --> 00:00:45.700
throughout the US that compared nivo-AVD to BV-AVD for six cycles in patients who had

00:00:45.700 --> 00:00:47.920
stage three and four Hodgkin lymphoma.

00:00:47.920 --> 00:00:54.140
GCSF was optional in the nivo-AVD arm, but it was required for the BV-AVD arm, and the

00:00:54.140 --> 00:00:55.020
primary endpoint was GCSF.

00:00:55.020 --> 00:01:04.040
This study did include patients that range all the way from age 12 to even patients that

00:01:04.040 --> 00:01:06.100
are in their 70s and 80s.

00:01:06.100 --> 00:01:13.740
So one of the great things about this study was that it was sort of obviously included

00:01:13.740 --> 00:01:20.960
patients that were below age 18, 25%, but over 60, about 10% of the patients.

00:01:20.960 --> 00:01:25.000
It did include some of the minority patients that we don't see.

00:01:25.000 --> 00:01:29.520
And a lot of the clinical trials, including Blacks and Hispanics, and also included some

00:01:29.520 --> 00:01:34.520
HIV patients.

00:01:34.520 --> 00:01:39.720
So if we look at first, looking at just the adverse event profile, neutropenia was more

00:01:39.720 --> 00:01:47.520
common in the nivo-AVD arm, probably because GCSF was not required and was only given in

00:01:47.520 --> 00:01:53.380
about 54% of the patients compared to 98% of the patients with BV-AVD.

00:01:53.380 --> 00:01:54.980
And as far as the anemia and thrombosis, it was very common.

00:01:54.980 --> 00:01:57.120
It was very common to see anemia, thrombosis, and thrombocytopenia, those numbers were quite

00:01:57.120 --> 00:01:59.640
similar.

00:01:59.640 --> 00:02:05.720
Despite having more neutropenia in the nivo-AVD arm, the febrile neutropenia rate, sepsis,

00:02:05.720 --> 00:02:12.860
and infections were less with the nivo-AVD arm compared to BV-AVD arm.

00:02:12.860 --> 00:02:19.120
As expected, peripheral neuropathy was higher in the BV-AVD arm, with grade three events

00:02:19.120 --> 00:02:24.960
in 8% compared to only 1% with nivo-AVD.

00:02:24.960 --> 00:02:32.020
But if you look at immune-related adverse events, which are of specific interest, there

00:02:32.020 --> 00:02:38.620
were patients with increased ASD-ALT that were seen, 7% who had grade three ASD-ALT

00:02:38.620 --> 00:02:44.260
elevation, and then everything else was pretty much 1% for grade three events, and included

00:02:44.260 --> 00:02:50.460
hypothyroid, pneumonitis, gastritis, and some colitis, and very, very few patients.

00:02:50.460 --> 00:02:54.940
However, the publication didn't go on.

00:02:54.940 --> 00:03:01.200
It didn't go over into specific details on how many total patients had grade three immune-related

00:03:01.200 --> 00:03:04.160
adverse events, etc.

00:03:04.160 --> 00:03:07.200
So that was one of the limitations.

00:03:07.200 --> 00:03:11.580
If you look at the three-year follow-up, the data still holds up, where the three-year

00:03:11.580 --> 00:03:15.080
PFS is 91% compared to 82%.

00:03:15.080 --> 00:03:24.920
It was 92% versus 83% at two years, so really no major changes a year later.

00:03:24.920 --> 00:03:31.900
And then, does not matter what age group you are, doesn't matter what IPS score is, doesn't

00:03:31.900 --> 00:03:38.220
matter what the stage is, or whether you have B symptoms or not, nivo-AVD benefited patients

00:03:38.220 --> 00:03:41.640
more than BV-AVD.

00:03:41.640 --> 00:03:48.180
And most importantly, the outcomes are poor for patients who are elderly in Hodgkin lymphoma,

00:03:48.180 --> 00:03:54.900
classically, but with this study, what we see is that the two-year PFS in age greater

00:03:54.900 --> 00:03:58.660
than BV-AVD is improved by 25% compared to BV-AVD.

00:03:58.660 --> 00:04:03.940
Additionally, there's improvement in overall survival for these patients.

00:04:03.940 --> 00:04:10.120
This is likely because more patients in the nivo-AVD arm were able to finish all six cycles

00:04:10.120 --> 00:04:14.740
without any dose reduction, so 69% versus 26%.

00:04:14.740 --> 00:04:21.020
The rate of discontinuation was quite low, 14% versus 55%, and non-relaxed mortality

00:04:21.020 --> 00:04:23.520
was 10% less with nivo-AVD.

00:04:23.520 --> 00:04:24.880
So this really accounts for...

00:04:24.880 --> 00:04:31.440
Why this regimen is so well-tolerated in this patient population.

00:04:31.440 --> 00:04:35.900
Now, so we went over the clinical trial data.

00:04:35.900 --> 00:04:41.140
Some of the questions that are not answered by a clinical trial is, you know, obviously,

00:04:41.140 --> 00:04:46.880
how does this data hold up in patients who are not on clinical trials?

00:04:46.880 --> 00:04:51.640
They tend to be a little bit more sicker, they probably have more autoimmune diseases,

00:04:51.640 --> 00:04:52.640
etc.

00:04:52.640 --> 00:04:54.860
Also, adverse events.

00:04:54.860 --> 00:04:56.800
They're usually more.

00:04:56.800 --> 00:05:00.600
And then what happens to these patients after they progress?

00:05:00.600 --> 00:05:05.740
So this study, which was just recently published by Dr. Bach, who is one of my colleagues at

00:05:05.740 --> 00:05:12.900
the University of Utah, included 327 patients across the whole U.S. that have been treated

00:05:12.900 --> 00:05:17.540
with nivo-AVD for advanced Hodgkin lymphoma.

00:05:17.540 --> 00:05:23.740
So this did include a lot of minority patients, so Hispanics, African-Americans, almost made

00:05:23.740 --> 00:05:24.840
up 30% of the population.

00:05:24.840 --> 00:05:32.640
This also included about 8% of the patients who had a history of an autoimmune condition.

00:05:32.640 --> 00:05:40.000
So this is obviously something that was not present in the SWOG study that we know of.

00:05:40.000 --> 00:05:44.180
So if you look at the adverse events first in this patient population, we do see a lot

00:05:44.180 --> 00:05:45.180
of nausea.

00:05:45.180 --> 00:05:51.120
And we do tend to see this more commonly in the younger patient with this nivo-AVD regimen,

00:05:51.120 --> 00:05:54.820
nausea affecting them more than elderly patients.

00:05:54.820 --> 00:05:59.820
So we do see a lot of nausea in the older patients, and we do also see a lot of nausea

00:05:59.820 --> 00:06:00.820
in the older patients.

00:06:00.820 --> 00:06:01.820
So we do see a lot of nausea in the older patients, and we do also see a lot of nausea

00:06:01.820 --> 00:06:02.820
in the younger patients.

00:06:02.820 --> 00:06:03.820
So we do see a lot of nausea in the older patients, and we do also see a lot of nausea

00:06:03.820 --> 00:06:04.820
in the older patients.

00:06:04.820 --> 00:06:05.820
So we do see a lot of nausea in the older patients, and we do also see a lot of nausea

00:06:05.820 --> 00:06:06.820
in the older patients.

00:06:06.820 --> 00:06:07.820
So we do see a lot of nausea in the older patients, and we do also see a lot of nausea

00:06:07.820 --> 00:06:08.820
in the older patients.

00:06:08.820 --> 00:06:09.820
So we do see a lot of nausea in the older patients, and we do also see a lot of nausea

00:06:09.820 --> 00:06:10.820
in the older patients.

00:06:10.820 --> 00:06:11.820
So we do see a lot of nausea in the older patients.

00:06:11.820 --> 00:06:41.800
So we do see a lot of nausea in the older patients, and we do also see a lot of nausea

00:06:41.800 --> 00:06:46.460
about 9% of the patients. They were in distribution similar to what was described

00:06:46.460 --> 00:06:54.440
in the SWOG study with hepatotoxicity being most common, followed by inflammatory arthritis,

00:06:54.880 --> 00:06:59.680
colitis, and adrenal insufficiency in about 1% of the patients. These are all grade three events.

00:06:59.680 --> 00:07:05.840
And if you look at any events, obviously there were pneumonitis and inflammatory arthritis that

00:07:05.840 --> 00:07:12.360
were also very common in this patient population. If you look at specifically in patients who had

00:07:12.360 --> 00:07:18.780
autoimmune conditions to start with, which is on the left, those patients, when they were

00:07:18.780 --> 00:07:25.200
challenged with NEVO-AVD, they did have more immune-related adverse events than other patients

00:07:25.200 --> 00:07:34.460
as expected. And as you can see, pretty much everyone had their inflammatory condition got

00:07:34.460 --> 00:07:35.220
worse, basically.

00:07:35.840 --> 00:07:41.760
While getting treatment with NEVO. And some had more than one immune-related adverse event.

00:07:42.700 --> 00:07:48.400
So this just gives us a little bit of data in terms of treating these patients with more

00:07:48.400 --> 00:07:54.240
precaution, especially if they're requiring a lot of systemic autoimmune therapy.

00:07:56.740 --> 00:08:02.600
PFS curve, one-year PFS was 95%. So pretty similar to what we would see, but obviously

00:08:02.600 --> 00:08:05.820
longer follow-up is required. And oral survival looks pretty good.

00:08:05.840 --> 00:08:12.400
And then lastly, this is some of the data that we're waiting to see in larger number of patients.

00:08:12.740 --> 00:08:22.960
About 17 patients progressed. And of them, six of them received BV plus chemo during salvage.

00:08:23.960 --> 00:08:30.700
Seven of them received immunotherapy plus chemo. And then two of them received BV-based treatment.

00:08:30.700 --> 00:08:35.820
And I think this is informational, but hopefully we'll get some more data with,

00:08:35.840 --> 00:08:40.740
larger number of patients in terms of what's done for patients who progress after NEVO-AVD,

00:08:40.740 --> 00:08:42.740
because the data is currently lacking.

00:08:42.740 --> 00:08:48.740
So in conclusion, with the SWOG study, obviously, NEVO-AVD is currently the standard of care

00:08:48.740 --> 00:08:54.740
in the United States. Obviously not everywhere in the country, not everywhere else in the world.

00:08:54.740 --> 00:09:00.740
Especially very well-tolerated at an age greater than 60, improves PFS by 10%.

00:09:00.740 --> 00:09:02.740
And if you look at the real-world utilization, the outcomes in terms of PFS are similar.

